CyRisk Secondary Technical Interview




Section 1: Docker


What command is used for running images as a container?

 docker ps -a
 sudo docker run -i -t alpine /bin/bash
 sudo docker run <container_name>
 All of the above


What is used for converting a pool of Docker hosts into a single, virtual Docker host?

 Docker Images
 Docker Compose
 Docker Hub
 Docker Swarm


What command is used for viewing all running containers?

 docker ps
 docker ps -a
 docker rm
 docker show

What command is used to go inside a running container?

 docker sh <container_id>
 docker exec -it <container_id> sh
 docker access <container_id>
 docker ps -a


What command is used to remove all stopped containers, unused networks, build caches, and dangling images?

 docker system kill -all
 docker kill -a
 docker system prune
 docker system rm -a


Section 2: Django

Which django admin command creates a new Django project.

django-admin startproject mysite
django-admin newproject mysite
django-admin startproject -n mysite .
django-admin createproject mysite


What manage.py commands are used for propagating changes you make to your models (adding a field, deleting a model, etc.) into your database schema.

python manage.py makechanges && python manage.py migrate
python manage.py makeupdates && python manage.py updatedb
python manage.py makemigrations && python manage.py migrate
python manage.py makemigrations && python manage.py updateschema


What part of django helps decoupled applications get notified when actions occur elsewhere in the framework. These allow certain senders to notify a set of receivers that some action has taken place. 

Action Hooks
Signals
Telegraph
Cross Site Scripting


Django’s default behavior is to run in autocommit mode. Each query is immediately committed to the database, unless a ___________ is active.

Transaction
Interface
Middleware
Application Firewall


Section 3: Javascript

Please complete the following inside a JS compiler

# Write a synchronous function ‘wait_1_second’ that returns a promise which resolves after a 1000ms delay. Write an asynchronous function that calls ‘wait_1_second’ and awaits the resolution of the returned promise.

Section 4: Python

Please complete the following problem inside a python compiler

# Implement a function `get_cve_score` that requests
# the cve details from the endpoint specified in the following pdf
# https://csrc.nist.gov/CSRC/media/Projects/National-Vulnerability-Database/documents/web%20service%20documentation/Automation%20Support%20for%20CVE%20Retrieval.pdf
# Examples
##########
# get_cve_score('CVE-2015-5611')
# {'base_score': 8.3}
#
# get_cve_score('CVE-2020-0506')
# {'base_score': 2.1}


